
git init                                - creating a git repository

git add .                               - adding updated files to a staging area before commit

git commit -m "<message>"               - making a commit

git log                                 - checking commit history

git branch                              - checking available branches

git branch <branch name>                - creating a branch

git checkout <branch name>              - moving to a new branch

git branch -m <old name> <new name>     - When in another branch

git branch -m <new name>                - When in a current branch

git branch -d branch_name               - Delete a branch of a local repo 


GITHUB

git remote add origin <your github url> -   give a label to a github repo e.g 'origin'
git push -u origin master               -   Pushing one branch from local repo to a github repo
git push -u origin --all                -   Pushing all branches from local repo to a github repo